                                             "designMd":  "---\nname: Linkage Digital System\ncolors:\n  surface: \u0027#fcf8ff\u0027\n  surface-dim: \u0027#dcd8e4\u0027\n  surface-bright: \u0027#fcf8ff\u0027\n  surface-container-lowest: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  surface-container-low: \u0027#f6f2fe\u0027\n  surface-container: \u0027#f0ecf8\u0027\n  surface-container-high: \u0027#eae6f3\u0027\n  surface-container-highest: \u0027#e4e1ed\u0027\n  on-surface: \u0027#1b1b23\u0027\n  on-surface-variant: \u0027#464554\u0027\n  inverse-surface: \u0027#302f39\u0027\n  inverse-on-surface: \u0027#f3effb\u0027\n  outline: \u0027#777586\u0027\n  outline-variant: \u0027#c7c4d7\u0027\n  surface-tint: \u0027#5148d7\u0027\n  primary: \u0027#2a14b4\u0027\n  on-primary: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  primary-container: \u0027#4338ca\u0027\n  on-primary-container: \u0027#c1beff\u0027\n  inverse-primary: \u0027#c3c0ff\u0027\n  secondary: \u0027#006c49\u0027\n  on-secondary: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  secondary-container: \u0027#6cf8bb\u0027\n  on-secondary-container: \u0027#00714d\u0027\n  tertiary: \u0027#7b0020\u0027\n  on-tertiary: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  tertiary-container: \u0027#a6002f\u0027\n  on-tertiary-container: \u0027#ffb0b4\u0027\n  error: \u0027#ba1a1a\u0027\n  on-error: \u0027#ffffff\u0027\n  error-container: \u0027#ffdad6\u0027\n  on-error-container: \u0027#93000a\u0027\n  primary-fixed: \u0027#e3dfff\u0027\n  primary-fixed-dim: \u0027#c3c0ff\u0027\n  on-primary-fixed: \u0027#100069\u0027\n  on-primary-fixed-variant: \u0027#372abf\u0027\n  secondary-fixed: \u0027#6ffbbe\u0027\n  secondary-fixed-dim: \u0027#4edea3\u0027\n  on-secondary-fixed: \u0027#002113\u0027\n  on-secondary-fixed-variant: \u0027#005236\u0027\n  tertiary-fixed: \u0027#ffdada\u0027\n  tertiary-fixed-dim: \u0027#ffb3b6\u0027\n  on-tertiary-fixed: \u0027#40000c\u0027\n  on-tertiary-fixed-variant: \u0027#920028\u0027\n  background: \u0027#fcf8ff\u0027\n  on-background: \u0027#1b1b23\u0027\n  surface-variant: \u0027#e4e1ed\u0027\ntypography:\n  display-lg:\n    fontFamily: Plus Jakarta Sans\n    fontSize: 48px\n    fontWeight: \u0027700\u0027\n    lineHeight: 56px\n    letterSpacing: -0.02em\n  headline-lg:\n    fontFamily: Plus Jakarta Sans\n    fontSize: 32px\n    fontWeight: \u0027600\u0027\n    lineHeight: 40px\n    letterSpacing: -0.01em\n  headline-md:\n    fontFamily: Plus Jakarta Sans\n    fontSize: 24px\n    fontWeight: \u0027600\u0027\n    lineHeight: 32px\n  headline-sm:\n    fontFamily: Plus Jakarta Sans\n    fontSize: 18px\n    fontWeight: \u0027600\u0027\n    lineHeight: 28px\n  body-lg:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 16px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 24px\n  body-md:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 14px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 20px\n  body-sm:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 12px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 16px\n  label-md:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 14px\n    fontWeight: \u0027500\u0027\n    lineHeight: 20px\n  label-sm:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 12px\n    fontWeight: \u0027600\u0027\n    lineHeight: 16px\n    letterSpacing: 0.05em\nrounded:\n  sm: 0.25rem\n  DEFAULT: 0.5rem\n  md: 0.75rem\n  lg: 1rem\n  xl: 1.5rem\n  full: 9999px\nspacing:\n  unit: 4px\n  sidebar-width: 240px\n  sidebar-collapsed: 64px\n  container-max: 1280px\n  gutter: 24px\n  margin-mobile: 16px\n  margin-desktop: 32px\n---\n\n## Brand \u0026 Style\nThe design system for Linkage Digital is built on the principles of **Precision, Clarity, and Modernity**. It targets professional environments where efficiency in time-tracking and employee management is paramount. The aesthetic borrows from the \"Linear\" school of designâ€”combining high-utility density with premium, minimalist finishes.\n\nThe emotional response should be one of focused calm. By utilizing high-quality geometric typography and a strictly governed neutral palette, the interface recedes into the background, allowing the user\u0027s data and tasks to take center stage. The style is **Modern Corporate**, characterized by subtle borders, intentional whitespace, and functional elevation.\n\n## Colors\nThe palette is dominated by a clean, off-white foundation to reduce eye strain during long working hours. \n\n- **Primary (Deep Indigo):** Used exclusively for high-intent actions, active navigation states, and primary brand moments.\n- **Success (Emerald):** Reserved for \"Clock-in\" actions, positive status indicators, and completed milestones.\n- **Destructive (Rose):** Used sparingly for errors, \"Clock-out\" (when used as a termination of a session), and destructive data actions.\n- **Neutrals:** A range of grays used to establish hierarchy. The background sits at #FAFAFA, while interactive surfaces use pure white #FFFFFF to \"pop\" against the floor.\n\n## Typography\nThis design system employs a dual-font strategy. **Plus Jakarta Sans** provides a confident, geometric personality for headings and large display text. **Inter** is used for all functional UI elements, data tables, and body copy to ensure maximum legibility at small sizes.\n\nFor mobile devices, `display-lg` and `headline-lg` should scale down by 20% (e.g., 48px to 38px) to maintain balance. Tabular data should strictly use `body-sm` or `body-md` with \"tabular-nums\" CSS styling enabled to ensure alignment in time-tracking columns.\n\n## Layout \u0026 Spacing\nThe layout follows a **Fixed-Fluid Hybrid** model. The sidebar is a fixed-width element (240px) that can collapse into a narrow icon-only bar (64px). The main content area uses a fluid grid with a maximum container width of 1280px to ensure readability on ultra-wide monitors.\n\nA strict 4px base unit governs all padding and margins. \n- **Desktop:** 32px outer margins with 24px gutters between grid items.\n- **Tablet:** 24px outer margins.\n- **Mobile:** 16px outer margins. Sidebar transforms into a bottom sheet or a full-screen overlay.\n\n## Elevation \u0026 Depth\nDepth is created through **Tonal Layering** and **Low-Contrast Outlines**. Instead of heavy shadows, the system uses 1px borders (#E5E7EB) to define boundaries.\n\n- **Level 0 (Floor):** #FAFAFA - The main application background.\n- **Level 1 (Card):** #FFFFFF - White surfaces with a very subtle 2px blur shadow (alpha 0.05) and a 1px solid border.\n- **Level 2 (Overlay/Modal):** #FFFFFF - Higher elevation with a 12px blur shadow (alpha 0.1) and a slightly darker border (#D1D5DB).\n- **Backdrop:** Use a 4px blur on the background layer when modals are active to maintain focus.\n\n## Shapes\nThe shape language is consistently \"Rounded\" to soften the professional tone. \n- **Small elements (Checkboxes, Tags):** 4px (rounded-sm).\n- **Standard elements (Buttons, Inputs, Cards):** 8px (base).\n- **Large elements (Modals, Feature Sections):** 16px (rounded-xl).\n- **Avatars:** Strictly circular to contrast against the geometric grid.\n\n## Components\n- **Buttons:** Primary buttons use the Indigo background with white text. Secondary buttons use a white background with a gray border and #18181B text. \"Clock-in\" buttons should utilize a subtle pulse animation or a soft Emerald glow.\n- **Input Fields:** 1px #E5E7EB border that transitions to #4338CA on focus. Use Inter 14px for input text. Label text sits above the field in `label-sm`.\n- **Time-Tracking Cards:** Use a high-contrast layout. The \"time\" display should use Plus Jakarta Sans Bold for prominence, while metadata (Project, Task) uses Inter.\n- **Sidebar:** Navigation items use a \"ghost\" style (no background) that transitions to a light Indigo tint (#EEF2FF) with Indigo text on active state.\n- **Status Chips:** Small, semi-transparent background tints of the status color (e.g., Emerald at 10% opacity) with high-saturation text for high glanceability.\n- **Data Tables:** No vertical borders. Use 1px horizontal dividers. Header row uses `label-sm` with a light gray background (#F9FAFB).",
